SWRC is located at Seronera within the worldfamous Serengeti National Park (SENAPA) and it is one of the centers of the Tanzania Wildlife Research Institute (TAWIRI). Singita Grumeti has been supporting conservation of the Serengeti ecosystem since 2003 and today we are bearing witness as they provide huge support for monitoring the Serengeti ecology, the SWRC Director, Dr Robert Fyumagwa said recently.Dr Fyumagwa was speaking shortly after Singita Grumeti had handed over a multi-million shillings worth vehicle to support the Serengeti Ecological Monitoring project.The project is being coordinated by Wake Forest University of USA, University of Glasgow (Scotland) and Nelson Mandela University.